3. Final Validation & State Checklist

To guarantee the system has reached the intended, secure, and reproducible end-state, verify the following via strict execution:

Kernel State: cat /proc/cmdline | grep "amdgpu.noretry=0" returns true. (Prevents hard hangs).

SELinux Integrity: ls -Zd ~/docker/*/* 2>/dev/null | grep -v container_file_t returns absolutely no output. (Ensures no hidden permission denied errors).

Internal API Security: curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://<LAN-IP>:11434 returns 000 (Connection Refused). (Proves Ollama is safely bound to localhost only).

HA Network Integrity: docker inspect homeassistant --format '{{.HostConfig.NetworkMode}}' returns host. (Proves mDNS/Discovery will function).

Hardware Acceleration: docker exec ollama ollama ps executed during a prompt returns 100% GPU in the Processor column. (Proves ROCm and GID mappings are active).

mcpo Permissions: stat -c "%u" ~/docker/mcpo/memory matches the numeric UID of your Nextcloud container. (Proves the AI can write files persistently).

Reverse Proxy Security: Accessing http://home.yourdomain.duckdns.org automatically redirects to https://, and the browser padlock verifies the Let's Encrypt certificate.

Conclusion & Rating

Score: 9.5 / 10

This is an expertly crafted deployment guide. It successfully bridges multiple complex networking boundaries (Bridge networks, Host networks, Nginx reverse proxying, and SELinux contexts) with surgical precision. The author correctly identifies obscure edge cases (e.g., Docker nftables dropping after firewalld reloads, RDNA3 Flash Attention bugs) and provides deterministic, command-line solutions for them.

The half-point deduction is strictly due to the truncated cron-job snippet in Appendix A, which breaks the copy-paste reproducibility for that specific optional module. Otherwise, this is production-grade documentation.

