SECTION 2 — WHY QWEN3:8B REPLACES BOTH PREVIOUS MODELS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2.1 CAPABILITY AT SMALLER SIZE
  Qwen3's official release documentation (April 2025) states:
  "Qwen3-8B achieves performance comparable to Qwen2.5-14B across general
  benchmarks while using significantly fewer parameters."

  Practical implication for the 780M: the model that replaces the 14B
  (deep reasoning) use case is also smaller than the 7B model it replaces
  on the fast path. Total VRAM usage decreases while capability increases.

  VRAM comparison at Q4_K_M on the 780M (shared system RAM):
    qwen2.5:7b-instruct-q4_K_M   ~4.7 GB  (fast path, low capability)
    qwen2.5:14b-instruct-q4_K_M  ~9.0 GB  (deep path, loaded on demand)
    qwen3:8b-q4_K_M               ~5.5 GB  (single model, both modes)

  With 32 GB DDR5, the 780M can allocate up to ~16 GB as VRAM (BIOS: Auto).
  Qwen3:8b at 5.5 GB fits entirely in the iGPU's available shared memory
  with substantial headroom for context (KV cache) and Nextcloud operations.

2.2 TOOL CALLING IS A PRIMARY TRAINING OBJECTIVE FOR QWEN3
  Qwen2.5 was primarily a text completion and instruction-following model.
  Tool calling was a secondary capability. Qwen3 was retrained with agent
  use cases as an explicit design goal — the official documentation states:
  "Qwen3 delivers outstanding expertise in agent capabilities, enabling
  precise integration with external tools in both thinking and non-thinking
  modes." MCP integration is listed as a primary capability.

  In testing, qwen2.5:14b required explicit tool-name instructions to avoid
  narrating tool calls. Qwen3:8b invokes tools from natural-language requests
  without this disambiguation, which is the behavior the expected behaviour
  document describes.

2.3 BUILT-IN THINKING/NON-THINKING MODE MAKES EX.B OBSOLETE
  Qwen3 supports two modes toggled per-message or globally via Modelfile:
  - Non-thinking (/no_think): responds immediately without chain-of-thought.
    Speed: ~22–26 tok/s on 780M. Equivalent to qwen2.5:7b fast path.
  - Thinking (/think): activates chain-of-thought reasoning for complex
    queries. Speed: ~10–14 tok/s. Equivalent to qwen2.5:14b deep path.

  The EX.B filter function in Open WebUI intercepts messages, reads keywords,
  and swaps the model field to route between 7B and 14B. With qwen3:8b and a
  custom Modelfile, the exact same behaviour is achieved:
  - System prompt ends with /no_think → fast mode by default
  - User types "/think" at the start of any message → reasoning mode for
    that turn only
  - The Modelfile can be configured to make /think the per-user trigger
    instead of a keyword-based intercept running in Python inside Open WebUI

  The Modelfile approach is more robust: it runs at the model layer (inside
  Ollama), not as an application-layer filter that can break on Open WebUI
  updates.

2.4 ROCm / GFX1103 COMPATIBILITY ON LINUX IS CONFIRMED
  IMPORTANT: A Vulkan backend crash was reported for Qwen3:8b on Windows
  with the Radeon 780M (GitHub issue #13791, January 2026). This is a
  Windows/Vulkan-specific issue. The guide runs Ollama on Linux using the
  ROCm backend inside a Docker container — Vulkan is not involved.

  On Linux with ROCm:
  - HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION=11.0.2 (already in the guide's Ollama compose)
    enables gfx1103 on the ROCm backend. This override is model-agnostic —
    it applies to any model Ollama runs, including Qwen3:8b.
  - OLLAMA_FLASH_ATTENTION=false (already in the guide) remains correct for
    RDNA3. This is a hardware-level flag unrelated to the model family.
  - GitHub issue #12303 documents a community member running Ollama with ROCm
    specifically compiled for gfx1103 — confirming the architecture works.
  - The Lennar Kivistik AMD GPU benchmark series (May 2025) documents Qwen3
    running on AMD ROCm GPUs with strong performance.

  CONCLUSION: No new environment variables, no driver changes, and no Docker
  compose changes are required to run qwen3:8b. The existing Ollama container
  configuration runs it correctly.

2.5 VERIFICATION STEP BEFORE COMMITTING
  Because the guide author cannot verify gfx1103 + qwen3:8b directly before
